parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
airbag system malfunction
failure of airbags to deploy in a crash
seat belt pretensioner malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall remedies can leave vehicles with safety-critical defects unrepaired, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but no parts available for repair
inability to trade or sell the vehicle due to outstanding recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission overheating warning light illuminates
the vehicle slows down or loses power
the vehicle stalls
and a whining or clunking noise is heard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission dipstick tube can cause transmission fluid leaks, leading to transmission failure and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The transmission dipstick tube breaks or fractures
and transmission fluid leaks are observed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience a loss of steering control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
the battery warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
and the vehicle may catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body sensor can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience a loss of acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle's acceleration is reduced
and the throttle body sensor fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and seatbelt system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly, or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the seatbelt warning indicator illuminates
and the airbags may deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience a loss of acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPMS can cause the driver to be unaware of low tire pressure, which can lead to tire failure, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: The TPMS light comes on
the tire pressure warning indicator illuminates
and the system fails to alert the driver of low tire pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank rollover valve can cause the fuel pump to shut off prematurely, leading to difficulty refueling, fuel leakage, and potential engine stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel pump clicks off prematurely
fuel splashes back out of the nozzle
difficulty refueling
fuel leakage
engine stalling
and strong smell of gasoline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel transfer tube can cause the engine to stall, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty refueling
fuel leakage
and strong smell of gasoline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system relay can cause the engine to stall, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine
and strong smell of gasoline.
